    "summary": "I am a researcher driven by microbial ecology and evolution. Currently, as a postdoc in MICROP consortium I am using multi-omics and modeling approaches with the aim to understand how plant-microbiome interactions are involved in alleviation of plant stresses. I am interested in the governing principles behind microbial community assembly.\n\nExpert in data science, bioinformatics, machine learning and research project design. Involved in several collaborations both with computational and experimental researchers. Able to independently design experiments for research and industry purposes. Collaborated with international and multidisciplinary teams (e.g. Marie Curie European Research Network, Chr. Hansen). Great management skills and able to perform high-quality research in an independent way. A fully committed person both in professional and personal projects (see Aman molli below). Previously, I worked in Greece, Austria, Denmark and Netherlands. I love to talk about science and to brainstorm about research with others in conferences or in a pub. \n\nAman molli: Founding member of a non-profit East-Mediterranean collective music group. We organized music concerts and workshops since 2016.",
